tuatara
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the only surviving representative of a group of reptiles which has otherwise been extinct for 100 million years, now found only on a few islands off New Zealand. [Maori]
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Environment
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [Ma. <b>tuatara</b> ancient reptile(<i>spenodon punctatus</i>)] cf. P.M. Ryan Dict. Modern Maori (1995) 273 (no macron).
